  "title": "Head of Customer Success",
  "description": "<p>The Role</p><p>As Head of Customer Success, you will own the post-sale customer lifecycle, driving</p><p>adoption, retention, expansion, and advocacy. You’ll build and lead a world-class CS</p><p>organisation, align it with revenue goals, and serve as the voice of the customer internally.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>Strategy & Vision</p><p>- Develop and execute a scalable Customer Success strategy aligned with company OKRs</p><p>(NRR, GRR, churn, upsell).</p><p>- Define customer segmentation (Enterprise, Mid-Market, SMB) and tailored success paths</p><p>(high-touch, low-touch, tech-touch).</p><p>- Establish success metrics, health scoring, and early-warning systems.</p><p>Team Leadership</p><p>- Hire, mentor, and manage a team of CSMs, Onboarding Specialists, and Renewals</p><p>Managers.</p><p>- Implement playbooks, career paths, and performance frameworks.</p><p>- Foster a data-driven, customer-obsessed culture.<br /></p><p>Customer Lifecycle Ownership</p><p>- Oversee onboarding, adoption, QBRs, renewals, and expansion motions.</p><p>- Partner with Product to influence roadmap via aggregated customer feedback.</p><p>- Collaborate with Sales on handoffs and Marketing on case studies/references.<br /></p><p>Revenue Impact</p><p>- Achieve targets for Net Revenue Retention (NRR > 120%), Gross Retention (>95%), and</p><p>upsell/cross-sell.</p><p>- Identify at-risk accounts and lead rescue missions.</p><p>- Build advocacy programmes (NPS > 50, testimonials, referrals).<br /></p><p>Operations & Systems</p><p>- Select and optimise CS tech stack (e.g., Gainsight, Salesforce, ChurnZero).</p><p>- Automate low-touch journeys and scale EBRs for high-value accounts.</p><p>- Report CS metrics to the executive team and board.</p>",
